Lubelski Wegiel Bogdanka SA (LWB) , Polandâ€™s
second-largest publicly traded coal producer, dropped for the
first time in four days as thermal coal prices fell.  The shares tumbled as much as 2.5 percent to 120.6 zloty,
and traded 1.7 percent lower at 121.6 zloty as of 10:41 a.m. in
Warsaw. The coal miner is the  second-best  performing stock in
the WIG20 Index this year, having risen 17 percent.  Thermal coal for 2013 delivery dropped 1.5 percent to
$98.35 a metric ton, the lowest since October 2009, according to
data compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
